    "text": "Now suppose c > 1/4. Then the sequence Xn defined by xo = 0 and Xn+1 = xh + c is strictly increasing and has no limit point. Thus if we define f on xo, x1 as any continuous function with equal values on the endpoints, and extend the definition from [xn, In+1| to |Xn+1, In+2] by the relation f(x) = f(x? + c), and extend the definition further to x < 0 by the relation f(x) = f(x), the resulting function has the desired property. Moreover, any function with that property clearly has this form.",
